<h2 id="fetching-the-coupon-information">Fetching the Coupon Information <a class="headerlink" href="validating-coupons#fetching-the-coupon-information" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Great! At this point, all <em>we</em> need to do is talk to Stripe and ask them:</p>
<blockquote><p>Hey Stripe! Is this a valid coupon code in your system?. Oh, and if it is,
  ow much is it for?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Since <code>Coupon</code> is just an object in Stripe's API, we can fetch it like <em>anything</em>
else. Booya!</p>
<p>As usual, add the API call in <code>StripeClient</code>. At the bottom, create a new public
function called <code>findCoupon()</code> with a <code>$code</code> argument:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="82f67e21d0">
    <div class="meta">
